OL,3,C100 years since the 'birth' of
OL,4,Ctelevision took place in Soho
OL,6,FToday, John's grandson Iain Logie
OL,7,FBaird unveiled a World Origin Site
OL,8,Fplaque at the cafe, to mark this
OL,9,Fmoment in history. He also officially
OL,10,Fopened a new 'Baird Room' which is
OL,11,Fdedicated to telling the story of
OL,12,Fwhere television first began.
OL,14,FIn January 1926, John invited a small
OL,15,Faudience into his workshop at 22 Frith
OL,16,FStreet, to see his latest invention.
OL,17,FHere, he showed that pictures could be
OL,18,Fsent and received using a system of
OL,19,Fspinning disks, light and electrical
OL,20,Fsignals.
