OL,3,C100 years since the 'birth' of
OL,4,Ctelevision took place in Soho
OL,6,FThis was a groundbreaking moment that
OL,7,Fmany historians now see as the point
OL,8,Fwhen television moved from a bold idea
OL,9,Fto reality.
OL,11,FTelevision historian, Professor Graeme
OL,12,FWest explains how the process worked:
OL,14,F"You had a spinning disk would focus a
OL,15,Flight on the subject. Then essentially
OL,16,Fwhat you're doing is your assessing
OL,17,Fthe intensity of that light spot and
OL,18,Fthen turning that into an electrical
OL,19,Fsignal.
